basics.name: Logan Wallace
basics.label: Computational Biologist
basics.summary: interesting in using computational skills and know how to solve biological problems.

Research and Professional Experience.name: Fred Hutch Cancer Center
Research and Professional Experience.summary: As a bioinformatician in the Meshinchi lab, I managed the world's largest pediatric AML dataset and co-lead all computational efforts to investigate genomic, transcriptomic and clinical data.

Volunteer Activity.summary: Mentored Seattle area high schools from underrepresented backgrounds in basic R programming and application of new skills to example biological problem.

projects.name: Quantum Computing
projects.summary: Quantum computing is the use of quantum-mechanical phenomena such as superposition and entanglement to perform computation. Computers that perform quantum computations are known as quantum computers.
